## Playwright e2e — only the Linux baselines (chromium-linux) are committed; they
## are the single source of truth and match CI (refresh via `npm run e2e:docker:update`).
## Baselines for any other platform (e.g. macOS chromium-darwin) are a local-only
## convenience for native iteration and must never be committed.
/e2e/__screenshots__/*
!/e2e/__screenshots__/chromium-linux
/test-results
/playwright-report
/blob-report
/.playwright
/e2e/vendor

## Local demo bundles — self-contained build of /define, rebuilt via `npm run demo:bundle`.
## The demos under demo/ reference these by relative path; the website's gulp "samples"
## task rewrites that path to the CDN URL on copy, so the file is never published or
## consumed by the website — it exists only for local testing against local changes.
/apex-grid.min.js
/apex-grid-enterprise.min.js
